# packages/wgpu-wasm/.gitignore — productionised merge of the archived legacy
# wasm-pack shims (naga + rhi-wgpu/crate; both packages were deleted in
# feat-20260511-naga-rhi-wgpu-merge M5 — this single crate replaces both,
# plan-strategy D-P1 + research F-2 / F-3 ship form).
#
# ufbx-style release (mirrors packages/fbx/.gitignore): the WHOLE pkg/ bundle
# is a wasm-pack build artefact and is NOT committed. wasm-bindgen emits pkg/ as
# an inseparable set — wgpu_wasm_bg.wasm + wgpu_wasm.js glue + wgpu_wasm.d.ts +
# wgpu_wasm_bg.wasm.d.ts + package.json — where the .js/.d.ts are hand-generated
# and cannot be regenerated from the .wasm alone, so committing "just the text"
# reintroduces the exact .d.ts-vs-rhi.rs drift this refactor removes.
#
# How pkg/ is populated (no checked-in copy → no drift possible):
# - Toolchain owners:  `pnpm -F @forgeax/engine-wgpu-wasm build:wasm` (build.sh,
#   wasm-pack; needs Rust — see CONTRIBUTING §Rust toolchain).
# - No-Rust consumers: `pnpm -F @forgeax/engine-wgpu-wasm fetch-wasm` downloads
#   the content-keyed pkg/ tarball from the `wasm-artifacts` GitHub Release
#   (scripts/fetch-wasm.mjs; also run non-fatally by root postinstall).
# - CI publishes that tarball on main push (publish-wgpu-wasm-release job).
#
# Cargo.lock = application-level crate lock, MUST be checked in (CI cache key =
#              hashFiles(.../Cargo.lock); bundle-size MetricKind cites the
#              resolved wgpu / naga patches from this file; also a content-key
#              input for the release asset name — see scripts/content-key.mjs).

target/
node_modules/

# Transient tarball written by scripts/fetch-wasm.mjs during download.
.pkg-fetch.tar.gz

# The whole wasm-pack output. Rebuilt by build.sh / fetched by fetch-wasm.mjs.
pkg/
